title: Tetrahedrally diminished dodecahedron
summary: In geometry, a tetrahedrally diminished[lower-alpha 1] dodecahedron (also tetrahedrally stellated icosahedron or propello tetrahedron[1]) is a topologically self-dual polyhedron made of 16 vertices, 30 edges, and 16 faces (4 equilateral triangles and 12 identical quadrilaterals).[2]
